## The M-5 Reporting Structure for MyClinic OpenMRS

---

### Report 1: Quarterly POA&M Status Report — To the AO

**Audience:** Executive Director (Authorizing Official)
**Frequency:** Quarterly (per Authorization Condition 3)
**Purpose:** Enable the AO to confirm that the authorization remains appropriate — that open risks are being managed, conditions are being met, and no material risk changes have occurred

**Format:** One-page executive summary with full POA&M attached as reference. The executive summary tells the story; the POA&M provides the detail for any item the AO wants to examine more closely.

